File: The logo of the Unemployment Insurance Fund. JOHANNESBURG - Payments from the government's COVID-19 relief scheme are expected to resume on Monday. Auditor-General Kimi Makwetu suspended the Temporary Employer-Employee Relief Scheme (Ters) for two weeks, after fraud claims. The UIF, which funds the scheme, says it would only pay out valid claims. [STATEMENT] Unemployment Insurance Fund to resume Covid-19 TERS payments early next week
Full statement: https://t.co/1tn4A0i21x #COVID19TERS #UIF pic.twitter.com/06BAwrG2IV Claims, where information is still outstanding, won't be automatically processed. READ: UIF to resume COVID-19 relief fund payments The benefit was put in place to help workers affected by the national lockdown. It formed part of President Cyril Ramaphosa's R500-billion economic and social relief package.